# REVIEW
# 1. high-level programming language
# 2. lists can be changed, tuples can't
# 3. it is a system of key-value pairs
# 4. the if statement's purpose is to check IF something is true and initiate the code within if it is
# 5. a loop is a conditional statement
# 6. a function doesn't need any object and is independent,
# while the method is a function, which is linked with any object
# 7. it allows you to use modules
# 8. it is a statement allowing you to handle errors without terminating the code
# 9. == is an equality operator, while is is and identity operator
# 10. len()'s purpose is to return the number of items in objects
